Quote: In shore sealing, some favourite haunt in a narrow rocky bay is watched by the sealer, ... until a sufficient number of the animals are together, and the water be low; the boat then approaches ... and as soon as land is made, a rush takes place up the beach. ... A blow in the snout with a club stuns ...
Notes: 1863 C.Heaphy `A Chapter on Sealing' Southern Monthly Magazine Vol I No 4 June pp173-176 in 1982 Richards Whaling and Sealing 4
